Reasoning: The paper deals with the detection of mesoscale structure in networks, which is a topic that falls under the purview of several sub-categories in computer science. The use of spectral methods and geodesic paths suggests that the paper may belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.SD (Software Engineering). The focus on network analysis and algorithms suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the use of objective functions and goodness-of-fit criteria suggests that the paper may belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
